 ## [Unreleased]
 
+> Prepared as **0.10.0** (minor, pre-1.0 policy) — held pending release cut from
+> `6034931`. Entries below are promoted to `## [0.10.0]` on tag.
+
+### Added
+
+- **Metered AI advisor tier** ([ADR-0007](docs/adr/0007-metered-ai-advisor-package.md)).
+  The three differentiated dashboard cards — peer **benchmarks**, the
+  **tax-credit** auto-hunter, and the **wealth-score** valuation — now offer
+  live, model-grounded "live reads" on top of their existing free static form,
+  and a new **"ask your books anything" concierge** lands as `POST /api/ask`
+  (`ConciergeThread` on the dashboard). The premium depth is delivered as
+  per-use token-metered operations (reusing the v0.9.0 economy — no subscription
+  tier): `insight-benchmarks` and `ask-ledger` cost 3 tokens, `insight-tax-credits`
+  and `insight-wealth` cost 5; all four surface through a shared `useMeteredAction`
+  hook with one loading / `402 "buy more"` / result state machine, and the free
+  cards stay free. **Grounding discipline:** every dollar figure is welded on
+  server-side from the pure ledger functions (`src/lib/ledger-tools`) — the model
+  writes prose only, so a hallucinated number can never reach the UI and a
+  concierge answer can't disagree with the dashboard. A deterministic fallback
+  runs wherever no model key is present, so keyless/CI builds stay fully demoable
+  (and the fallback path is the unit-tested one). New routes
+  `/api/insights/{benchmarks,tax-credits,wealth}`; new `OPERATIONS` rate-card
+  lines.
+- **Provider-agnostic LLM seam** (`src/lib/ai/`). A single `generateText()`
+  call-site behind `LLM_PROVIDER` drives every AI route: **Gemini** (default,
+  `@google/generative-ai`) or **Claude** (the Claude Code CLI in headless mode
+  against a local Pro/Max subscription — no API key, local dev only). Providers
+  are dynamically imported so only the selected engine's deps load, and results
+  carry provider-honest provenance (`gemini` / `claude` / `fallback`) across
+  insights, the concierge, and categorize. New env keys `LLM_PROVIDER`,
+  `CLAUDE_MODEL`, `CLAUDE_CLI_BIN`, `CLAUDE_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS`, `CLAUDE_CLI_EXTRA_ARGS`.
+- **Multi-environment database layer** (`src/lib/db/`). One Postgres dialect over
+  three drivers behind `getDb()` — **PGlite** (embedded WASM, file-backed; local
+  dev with no cloud or Docker), **pg** over `DATABASE_URL` (Supabase / generic
+  Postgres), and the **Cloud SQL** connector (GCP). The driver is auto-detected
+  or forced via `DB_DRIVER`; the token ledger and auth are refactored onto it.
+  Ships the first migration (`migrations/0001_init.sql`) with `npm run db:setup` /
+  `db:reset`. New env keys `DB_DRIVER`, `PGLITE_PATH`, `INSTANCE_CONNECTION_NAME`.
+- **Local dev-auth** (`DEV_AUTH`). Loosens local auth to a fixed dev user (no
+  OAuth round-trip) so the full token-metering path runs end-to-end against local
+  PGlite. A `docs/SETUP.md` runbook and a `npm run polar:setup` bundle-provisioning
+  helper are added.
+- **Playwright journey e2e suite** driving the real stack (dev-auth + PGlite + the
+  AI provider): landing, dashboard, metered insight reads, the concierge,
+  billing/FAQ, and the paywall (`e2e/01-landing` … `e2e/05-billing-faq`,
+  `zz-paywall`), alongside the existing regression guards.
+
+### Changed
+
+- `/api/categorize` and the new advisor routes now share the extracted
+  `generateText()` seam rather than an inline Gemini call, with a deterministic
+  fallback on every route. Unit suite grows to **138 tests** (+32: advisor
+  `narrate` parsers and fallbacks, `ledger-tools`, the concierge intent router,
+  and economy rate-card costs).
+
+### Fixed
+
+- `wealth-score/lib/compute` imported the `@/features/benchmarks` barrel, pulling
+  the component graph (`next/link`) into a pure compute module — switched to a
+  deep import so the pure module stays free of UI dependencies.
+
